            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab><persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Deusdedit"
                            >Deusdede</name></persName> vir venerabilis <rs key="#Priests"
                            >presbitero</rs>, <persName key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Deusdona"
                                >Deusdona</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> germano eius, simul et <persName
                            key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Filipertus">Filipert</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> cum filio suo <persName
                            key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Willibertus">Wilipert</name></persName>
                        (…) in proprietas nostra sicut virtus admiset <rs key="#Private_foundations"
                            >a fundamentis</rs> vestiboli in honore Deo et <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Private_foundations" ref="#juridical_persons/230">beati
                            Petri apostoli</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Churches">eclesia</rs> construximus, ubi omnem ispem nostra
                        posuimus. Post hec vero, Christo protigente, ipsa Dei eclesia ividem in loco
                        Ansulari construxissemus, previdimus ividem offerere Deo et ipsiei eclesie:
                        in primis, <rs key="#Casalini/fundamenta">fundaminto</rs> ubi ipse Dei
                        eclesia edita vel fabrita videtur esset, cum <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> illa et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> que iuxta ipsa Dei eclesia havere
                        videmur, in integrum; simulque et inter <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs> et terra
                        inivi ad nus offerta esse volomus in suprascripto loco <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Casalini/fundamenta #Landed_possessions #Size #Wine #Churches #Private_foundations"
                            >Ansulari</placeName>, idest <rs key="#Size">modiorum sex</rs>.
                            <foreign>Si riservano l’usufrutto vitalizio dei beni donati da loro e di
                            quanto</foreign> ad alios christeanos hominis data vel offerta fueret,
                            <foreign>impegnandosi</foreign> inivi in ipsa Dei eclesia officium
                        faciendi et laudem Deo referendi. <foreign>La gestiranno</foreign> per
                        comune consilio (…) tamquam bonus germanus qui de uno germine sunt
                        procreatos ut nus in bonis operibus et ipsei eclesie Dei autilitas unus
                        alterius que recte locutus fueret, nus audire vocis diveamus, faciendum
                        adque adinplendum. De ordinationem vero de suprascripta Dei eclesia sic esse
                        inistituimus ut, dum nus Dominus in hoc seculo conservaveret, ut supra
                        dictum est, per comune conslio semper facere diveamus; et si qualiter Deo
                        fuerit preceptionem et unus aut plures de nus de seculo recesseret, ille qui
                        de nus supervixerit simeliter et ordinationem et alias suprascriptas
                        capitulas facias, omnia per comune consilio sicut supra decrevimus.
                            <foreign>Divieto di dividere i beni della chiesa o di sottrarli. Divieto
                            di</foreign> nulla femina adducendi, qui ivi havitare diveas.
                            <foreign>Pena</foreign>: in auri solidos quinientum. (…) Et pro
                        confirmationem <persName key="#Writer"><name ref="David"
                            >David</name></persName> iscrivere rogavimus. Actum <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitate</rs> ista <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/4"
                            >Lucense</placeName>. <foreign>Sottoscrizioni</foreign>: Deusdede in Dei
                        nomine presbiter (ss); Deusdona clericus (ss); + Filipert clerici; +
                        Wilipert item <rs key="#Other_clerics">clerici</rs> filio eius; <persName
                            key="#Witness #Priests"><name ref="Baruncius">Baruncio</name></persName>
                                <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> (ss); <persName key="#Witness #Priests"><name ref="Gausbertus"
                                >Gauspertu</name></persName>
                                <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> (ss); + <persName key="#Witness #Priests"><name ref="Warimbertus"
                                >Warnipert</name></persName> viri venerabilis <rs key="#Priests"
                                    >presbiteri</rs> testis; + <persName key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name ref="Prandulus"
                                >Pranduli</name></persName> filio quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Causulus">Causuli</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis; +
                                <persName key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name ref="Audibertus">Audipert</name></persName> filio
                                <persName><name ref="Offulus">Offuli</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis. </ab>
